# 🚀 Backend Rule — FastAPI (Clean + DRY)

## 🎯 Goal
Write clean, maintainable, and scalable backend code using:
- DRY
- KISS
- YAGNI
- Early Return
- Clean Architecture

---

## 🧠 Core Principles

### DRY (Don't Repeat Yourself)
- Never duplicate logic
- If repeated 2x → extract to function/service/decorator/helper

### KISS (Keep It Simple)
- Prefer simple solutions over complex abstractions
- Avoid unnecessary layers

### YAGNI (You Aren’t Gonna Need It)
- Do NOT implement future features
- Only build what is required NOW

### Early Return
- Avoid nested ifs
- Always fail fast and return early

### SRP (Single Responsibility)
- One function = one responsibility
- One class = one purpose

---

## 🧩 Architecture (MANDATORY)

Follow strict separation:

- Router → orchestration only (NO logic)
- Service → business logic
- Repository → data access
- Dependency → object creation

---

## 🚫 Router Rules (FastAPI)

Routers MUST be thin:

❌ Forbidden:
- Business logic
- DB access
- Data transformation

✅ Allowed:
- Input validation (Pydantic)
- Call service
- Return response

Example:

```python
@router.post("/")
async def create(data: Schema, service: Service = Depends(get_service)):
    return await service.create(data)
```

---

## 🔥 Service Rules

- Contains ALL business logic
- Must be reusable
- Must NOT depend on FastAPI

Use:
- Early return
- Fail fast validation

---

## 🗄 Repository Rules

- Only DB logic
- No business rules
- Use BaseRepository to avoid repetition

---

## ♻️ Reusability (MANDATORY)

Always prefer reuse via:

- Base classes (BaseRepository, BaseService)
- Helpers (utils)
- Decorators (error handling, logging)
- Dependencies (DI)

---

## ⚡ Decorators

Use decorators for cross-cutting concerns:
- Error handling
- Logging
- Authorization

---

## 🧠 Code Style

### Explicit > Magic
- Prefer readable code over clever code

### Readability > Performance
- Optimize only when necessary

### Consistency > Perfection
- Follow project patterns strictly

---

## ❌ Anti-Patterns (FORBIDDEN)

- Fat controllers
- Duplicated validation
- Inline DB queries in routers/services
- Premature abstraction
- Overengineering
- Deep nesting (if inside if inside if)

---

## ✅ Good Practices

- Use @property for derived fields
- Use dependency injection everywhere
- Use typed schemas (Pydantic)
- Use small, composable functions

---

## 🔥 Golden Rule

If you copy/paste code → STOP and refactor

---

## 🧠 Mindset

Code is read more than written.

Always optimize for:
- Clarity
- Maintainability
- Simplicity
